WEBVTT

00:09.843 --> 00:11.886
<i>Previously on "The Continental"...</i>

00:11.886 --> 00:14.639
<i>What Frankie took
is very important.</i>

00:14.639 --> 00:16.558
Find your brother,
'cause if you don't,

00:16.558 --> 00:18.643
I'll bring the weight of this
whole institution

00:18.643 --> 00:19.686
down on you both.

00:19.686 --> 00:21.229
[alarm blares[

00:23.898 --> 00:26.359
- Where is the coin press?
- Frankie took it.

00:26.359 --> 00:28.737
You thought you could
outsmart the High Table--

00:28.737 --> 00:30.196
foolish.

00:30.196 --> 00:31.656
<i>Running guns, I'm guessing.</i>

00:31.656 --> 00:33.700
Were you close
with them over there?

00:33.700 --> 00:35.869
If you need someone
in charge of saving your life,

00:35.869 --> 00:37.203
I'll take Frankie every time.

00:37.203 --> 00:38.913
We made a promise to Dad.

00:38.913 --> 00:41.416
This was his dojo, but now
it's just some money pit

00:41.416 --> 00:43.001
that you can't seem to let go.

00:43.001 --> 00:45.253
You made a big fucking
mistake coming here, Winston.

00:45.253 --> 00:47.714
We're all running now,
but I can help you--

00:47.714 --> 00:49.007
both of you.

00:49.007 --> 00:50.300
Trust me.

00:50.300 --> 00:51.885
So you think
I'm just gonna drop a case

00:51.885 --> 00:53.386
and go back to making it
with you

00:53.386 --> 00:54.888
like this conversation
never happened?

00:54.888 --> 00:55.930
My job is to fuck you.

00:55.930 --> 00:57.474
Look, I'm looking
for the supplier.

00:57.474 --> 00:59.017
<i>His name is Francis Scott,
and he is a ghost.</i>

00:59.017 --> 01:01.936
- We have no authority here.
- It's time to outsource.

01:01.936 --> 01:04.898
Perhaps some of our guests
are available--the twins.

01:04.898 --> 01:06.358
<i>Get me those twins.</i>

01:06.358 --> 01:08.693
You both need
to look after each other.

01:08.693 --> 01:11.029
They want me and this!

01:11.029 --> 01:12.822
Frankie!

01:12.822 --> 01:15.825
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

01:15.825 --> 01:17.452
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:17.452 --> 01:21.623
I need guns, lots of guns.

01:24.376 --> 01:27.504
[siren wailing]

01:33.593 --> 01:36.721
[stick rattling]

01:36.721 --> 01:42.519
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:45.271 --> 01:47.357
Let me get that rag.

01:48.983 --> 01:51.319
- Let me do it.
- No way.

01:51.319 --> 01:53.279
You said yourself
I'm the one with the arm.

01:53.279 --> 01:55.240
And who struck you
out twice last week?

01:55.240 --> 01:58.243
You keep bringing that up,
I ain't gonna let you do shit.

01:58.243 --> 01:59.828
It ain't just about that.

01:59.828 --> 02:01.955
Why, 'cause I'm younger?

02:01.955 --> 02:04.708
[coughs]
Damn kid.

02:06.751 --> 02:09.713
What even bring me for--
just so I can carry the rag?

02:09.713 --> 02:11.798
All right, fine.

02:11.798 --> 02:13.758
You better be
Whitey goddamn Ford

02:13.758 --> 02:15.010
with this,

02:15.010 --> 02:17.220
or Cormac's gonna have our ass,
you hear me?

02:17.220 --> 02:20.181
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:20.181 --> 02:22.017
Watch your hand, Winston.

02:22.017 --> 02:25.186
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:25.186 --> 02:28.356
Go.

02:28.356 --> 02:35.488
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:35.488 --> 02:38.742
[indistinct shouting
in Spanish]

02:38.742 --> 02:40.118
<i>Fuego!</i>

02:40.118 --> 02:42.328
[person screaming]

02:42.328 --> 02:44.497
- [gasps]
<i>- Ayúdame!</i>

02:44.497 --> 02:47.083
[voice breaking]
There's people in there.

02:47.083 --> 02:49.169
- Run.
<i>- Ayúdame!</i>

02:49.169 --> 02:51.671
Frankie, there's
people in there.

02:51.671 --> 02:54.758
[glass shattering,
shouting continues]

02:54.758 --> 03:01.139
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:01.139 --> 03:03.350
Winston, run!

03:03.350 --> 03:06.519
<i>[siren wailing]</i>

03:14.152 --> 03:15.362
Hey.

03:15.362 --> 03:17.530
- The brother?
- Yeah.

03:17.530 --> 03:21.284
- Yeah, that's him.
- Personal effects.

03:21.284 --> 03:23.286
Thanks, Ezra.

03:31.586 --> 03:33.797
We don't have much time.

03:38.885 --> 03:45.809
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:56.236 --> 03:59.322
[breathes deeply]

03:59.322 --> 04:06.454
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:45.660 --> 04:49.372
<i>[Baby Huey & The Babysitters'
"Hard Times"]</i>

04:49.372 --> 04:56.463
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:56.463 --> 04:59.424
<i>♪ Cold, cold eyes upon me ♪</i>

04:59.424 --> 05:01.718
<i>♪ They stare ♪</i>

05:01.718 --> 05:06.306
<i>♪ People all around me,
and they're all in fear ♪</i>

05:07.432 --> 05:11.853
<i>♪ They don't seem to want me,
but they won't admit ♪</i>

05:11.853 --> 05:14.481
<i>♪ I must be
some kind of creature ♪</i>

05:14.481 --> 05:18.193
<i>♪ Up here having fits ♪</i>

05:18.193 --> 05:22.197
<i>♪ From my party house,
I'm afraid to come outside ♪</i>

05:22.197 --> 05:24.699
<i>♪ Although I'm filled
with love ♪</i>

05:24.699 --> 05:28.119
<i>♪ I'm afraid
they'll hurt my pride ♪</i>

05:28.119 --> 05:33.333
<i>♪ So I play the part
I feel they want of me ♪</i>

05:33.333 --> 05:35.585
<i>♪ And I pull the shades ♪</i>

05:35.585 --> 05:38.630
<i>♪ So I won't see them
seeing me ♪</i>

05:38.630 --> 05:41.341
<i>♪ Having hard times ♪</i>

05:41.341 --> 05:43.802
<i>♪ In this crazy town ♪</i>

05:43.802 --> 05:46.721
<i>♪ Having hard times ♪</i>

05:46.721 --> 05:53.520
<i>♪ There's no love
to be found ♪</i>

05:53.520 --> 05:56.731
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:58.024 --> 06:00.985
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

06:00.985 --> 06:07.951
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:58.710 --> 07:05.008
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:05.008 --> 07:07.802
<i>♪ You were four,
and I was six ♪</i>

07:07.802 --> 07:10.680
<i>♪ Rode on horses
made of sticks ♪</i>

07:10.680 --> 07:12.932
<i>♪ You wore black,
and I wore white ♪</i>

07:12.932 --> 07:14.809
<i>♪ You would always win
the fight ♪</i>

07:14.809 --> 07:17.854
<i>♪ Bang, bang,
you shot me down ♪</i>

07:17.854 --> 07:20.648
<i>[muffled] * Bang, bang,
I hit the ground ♪</i>

07:20.648 --> 07:22.984
<i>♪ Bang, bang,
that awful sound ♪</i>

07:22.984 --> 07:28.656
<i>♪ Bang, bang,
my baby shot me down ♪</i>

07:28.656 --> 07:31.326
<i>♪ You grew up,
and I left town ♪</i>

07:31.326 --> 07:33.828
<i>♪ I would always call
you mine ♪</i>

07:33.828 --> 07:36.998
<i>♪ You would always laugh
and say ♪</i>

07:36.998 --> 07:39.376
<i>♪ "Remember
when we used to play?" ♪</i>

07:39.376 --> 07:41.628
<i>♪ Bang, bang,
you shot me down ♪</i>

07:41.628 --> 07:44.631
[distorted voices]

07:44.631 --> 07:47.801
<i>[heartbeat thumping]</i>

07:58.353 --> 07:59.938
[button clicks]

08:02.190 --> 08:05.443
[clicking]

08:05.443 --> 08:12.575
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:21.084 --> 08:23.837
<i>♪ Till the day
I don't know why ♪</i>

08:23.837 --> 08:26.589
<i>♪ Sit alone, sometimes I cry ♪</i>

08:26.589 --> 08:29.884
<i>♪ Wouldn't even try to lie
about the times ♪</i>

08:29.884 --> 08:31.261
<i>♪ Come inside ♪</i>

08:31.261 --> 08:33.888
<i>♪ Bang, bang,
you shot me down ♪</i>

08:33.888 --> 08:36.891
<i>♪ Bang, bang,
I hit the ground ♪</i>

08:36.891 --> 08:38.810
<i>♪ Bang, bang,
that awful sound ♪</i>

08:38.810 --> 08:40.603
<i>♪ Bang, bang ♪</i>

08:45.275 --> 08:48.153
[distant siren wailing]

08:50.989 --> 08:55.035
Put it right over there.

08:55.035 --> 08:57.162
Hey!

08:57.162 --> 08:59.998
What the fuck are y'all doing
in my dojo?

08:59.998 --> 09:03.376
[distant car horns honking]

09:03.376 --> 09:05.253
Hey!

09:05.253 --> 09:08.923
That ain't mine!
You got the wrong address!

09:08.923 --> 09:10.175
Hey!

09:10.175 --> 09:12.385
That ain't mine.

09:12.385 --> 09:14.512
Hey!
Who do you work for?

09:14.512 --> 09:16.348
Not you, bitch.

09:24.147 --> 09:26.232
Burton, huh?

09:26.232 --> 09:27.734
Shit.

09:27.734 --> 09:29.361
You're faster than they say.

09:29.361 --> 09:32.697
You're new here?
Chen know about this?

09:32.697 --> 09:33.907
Chen's gone.

09:33.907 --> 09:36.826
New rules, my rules.

09:36.826 --> 09:39.788
In this neighborhood, everyone
gets a cigarette machine.

09:39.788 --> 09:41.998
My father and Chen
had an understanding.

09:41.998 --> 09:43.708
He stayed
out of my father's business,

09:43.708 --> 09:45.794
and we stayed out of his.

09:45.794 --> 09:47.587
It's a little more complex
than that.

09:47.587 --> 09:50.131
Well, here's my rule.

09:50.131 --> 09:54.344
You mess with my place,
you messing with my family.

09:55.845 --> 09:59.474
I'm a businessman.
You're a businesswoman.

09:59.474 --> 10:04.104
Focus on your business,
not picking up broken glass.

10:04.104 --> 10:07.107
<i>[Gerry Rafferty's
"Baker Street"]</i>

10:07.107 --> 10:09.651
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:09.651 --> 10:11.444
Weiko!

10:11.444 --> 10:17.325
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:17.325 --> 10:20.745
[knock at door]

10:20.745 --> 10:22.706
Hi.
It's me.

10:22.706 --> 10:26.584
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:26.584 --> 10:27.877
What?

10:27.877 --> 10:29.587
You're not answering
your phone.

10:29.587 --> 10:33.174
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:33.174 --> 10:37.262
Look, what the hell
are you doing, huh?

10:37.262 --> 10:39.723
It's Tuesday.

10:39.723 --> 10:41.391
Fucking Tuesday.

10:41.391 --> 10:43.476
You know what? This is exactly
what I'm talking about.

10:43.476 --> 10:45.311
You think you can just
break into my house,

10:45.311 --> 10:46.438
drop off some file,

10:46.438 --> 10:47.897
and everything
just goes back to normal?

10:47.897 --> 10:49.024
I'm trying to help you

10:49.024 --> 10:50.817
with your little
investigation here.

10:50.817 --> 10:52.277
Thought you'd appreciate it.

10:52.277 --> 10:54.154
Your guy's MIA, so you can stop
your little goose chase.

10:54.154 --> 10:55.947
You know, I don't need
your help, and he's not MIA.

10:55.947 --> 10:57.365
- No?
- No.

10:57.365 --> 11:00.201
How do you know that?
You saw him?

11:00.201 --> 11:02.287
- No.
- How do you know that?

11:02.287 --> 11:03.705
I got a hunch.

11:03.705 --> 11:07.792
[laughs] A detective
with a hunch--that's original.

11:07.792 --> 11:09.085
You know what?
Screw you.

11:09.085 --> 11:11.087
Just tell me why you're
so fixated on the guy.

11:11.087 --> 11:12.672
You know, I thought
we had an agreement.

11:12.672 --> 11:14.883
I don't ask about your family,
and you don't ask me about--

11:14.883 --> 11:16.509
This is different than that,
and you know it.

11:16.509 --> 11:17.677
It's not different.

11:17.677 --> 11:19.637
Stay out of my
personal business.

11:19.637 --> 11:22.766
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:22.766 --> 11:24.184
I didn't come here
to argue with you.

11:24.184 --> 11:25.852
No, I know exactly
what you came here for.

11:25.852 --> 11:27.020
- Oh, you do?
- Yep.

11:27.020 --> 11:28.355
It's the perfect relationship.

11:28.355 --> 11:29.856
- [chuckles derisively]
- Okay.

11:29.856 --> 11:31.483
Keep our side shit out of it.
Copy that.

11:31.483 --> 11:34.694
- Yeah. No. No, no, no, no.
- Shh, shh, shh, come here.

11:34.694 --> 11:36.529
I'm sorry.

11:36.529 --> 11:41.034
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:41.034 --> 11:44.204
[telephone ringing]

11:44.204 --> 11:48.792
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:48.792 --> 11:50.043
[sighs]

11:50.043 --> 11:52.379
[receiver clatters]
Hello?

11:52.379 --> 11:53.797
Speaking.

11:53.797 --> 12:00.804
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:00.804 --> 12:03.473
Francis Scott?

12:05.600 --> 12:07.811
You sure it's him?

12:07.811 --> 12:11.981
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:11.981 --> 12:14.359
[exhales sharply]

12:14.359 --> 12:15.610
No, no, no, no.

12:15.610 --> 12:17.696
Uh, just, uh, uh,
give me a moment.

12:17.696 --> 12:19.072
I'll be there, all right?

12:19.072 --> 12:21.616
Thank you.
Thank you.

12:21.616 --> 12:28.581
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:28.581 --> 12:31.167
Look, this maybe don't help
take the pain away,

12:31.167 --> 12:36.006
but word on the street is that
Frankie got the last laugh.

12:37.424 --> 12:40.093
Chest was empty.

12:40.093 --> 12:43.013
W-what do you mean empty?

12:43.013 --> 12:44.764
[music stops]

12:44.764 --> 12:47.058
I mean whatever
they killed him for,

12:47.058 --> 12:48.727
they never got it.

12:48.727 --> 12:51.730
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

12:51.730 --> 12:53.314
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:53.314 --> 12:55.859
Everything's always
on Frankie's terms.

12:55.859 --> 13:01.364
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:03.783 --> 13:07.120
I feel
like somebody should...

13:07.120 --> 13:09.664
say something.

13:09.664 --> 13:11.207
I can say a little--

13:11.207 --> 13:14.210
I'm going to kill Cormac,
and I need all of you.

13:14.210 --> 13:18.173
I was thinking more
like a prayer or something.

13:18.173 --> 13:20.925
Cormac is on
a different level now, Winston.

13:20.925 --> 13:23.178
You so much as spit
on his stoop,

13:23.178 --> 13:25.638
every freak in and around
that hotel will be after you.

13:25.638 --> 13:27.640
My point exactly.

13:27.640 --> 13:29.225
Coin press is still missing.

13:29.225 --> 13:31.311
They're gonna come after
anyone who ever knew Frankie.

13:31.311 --> 13:32.979
We had nothing
to do with this.

13:32.979 --> 13:34.981
He's desperate.
We have to strike first.

13:34.981 --> 13:36.775
Let's just give him
what he wants.

13:36.775 --> 13:38.109
Let this beef die with Frankie.

13:38.109 --> 13:39.527
I don't have it,

13:39.527 --> 13:41.780
and I have no clue where
Frankie would have hidden it.

13:41.780 --> 13:44.199
And they will kill all of us
before they realize that.

13:44.199 --> 13:46.034
It ain't as simple
as taking him out.

13:46.034 --> 13:48.953
We still got to deal
with The Continental.

13:48.953 --> 13:50.747
A takeover...

13:50.747 --> 13:52.749
of the whole hotel?

13:52.749 --> 13:54.376
Listen...

13:54.376 --> 13:58.129
if we kill Cormac,
we're not only taking his life.

13:58.129 --> 14:00.340
We are taking his goddamn house

14:00.340 --> 14:04.177
and everything that comes
with it...

14:04.177 --> 14:07.138
including his hold
on the gun-running game.

14:07.138 --> 14:09.766
That's right.
Everything will go through you.

14:09.766 --> 14:11.434
No longer
will you be a middleman

14:11.434 --> 14:14.187
living outside the system--
you will be the system.

14:14.187 --> 14:16.022
How are we supposed
to believe

14:16.022 --> 14:17.899
a guy in an ascot
can pull this off?

14:17.899 --> 14:20.360
That's simple--
because I know Cormac.

14:20.360 --> 14:22.862
I know how he operates,
how he thinks,

14:22.862 --> 14:24.322
how he manipulates people,

14:24.322 --> 14:28.076
because as a kid,
he did it to me and Frankie.

14:28.076 --> 14:31.371
We were his errand boys.
We thought he was a god.

14:31.371 --> 14:33.373
That's not gonna be enough.

14:33.373 --> 14:35.709
Well, I also have
a lot of money,

14:35.709 --> 14:39.629
problem-solving money,
enough to build an army.

14:39.629 --> 14:41.381
I was planning on starting
a new life with it.

14:41.381 --> 14:43.508
[door opens]

14:45.927 --> 14:48.221
What did she say?

14:48.221 --> 14:51.391
She wants to know
where Frankie is.

14:51.391 --> 14:53.309
Frankie.

14:53.309 --> 14:54.561
Uh-oh.

14:54.561 --> 15:01.568
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:21.880 --> 15:25.425
- [screams]
- Stop.

15:25.425 --> 15:26.885
Lemmy--

15:26.885 --> 15:28.845
Jesus.
[choking]

15:28.845 --> 15:30.680
Look...

15:30.680 --> 15:33.099
Okay, okay.
Hold on. Hold on a second.

15:33.099 --> 15:34.601
Let me explain, all right?

15:34.601 --> 15:38.938
We had no time.
I had to move quickly, okay?

15:38.938 --> 15:40.148
Stop!

15:40.148 --> 15:41.608
Stop, stop, stop!

15:41.608 --> 15:42.650
Wait, back off.

15:44.194 --> 15:46.738
You had no right.

15:46.738 --> 15:48.656
I know.

15:48.656 --> 15:49.908
I'm sorry.

15:49.908 --> 15:52.369
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:52.369 --> 15:55.121
Hold on, hold on, hold on.
Get back.

15:55.121 --> 15:58.166
[both straining]

15:58.166 --> 16:05.340
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:10.845 --> 16:12.597
Yen, I'm sorry.

16:12.597 --> 16:14.307
Yen, wait.

16:14.307 --> 16:15.809
What, uh--
[door opens]

16:15.809 --> 16:17.936
Sorry.
[door slams]

16:17.936 --> 16:20.021
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:20.021 --> 16:22.816
If we're gonna take on
The Continental,

16:22.816 --> 16:25.151
we're gonna need her.

16:25.151 --> 16:28.405
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:28.405 --> 16:32.242
[distant siren wailing]

16:37.872 --> 16:40.583
Francis Patrick Scott. Yep.

16:40.583 --> 16:42.794
Okay, yeah,
where the hell is he now?

16:42.794 --> 16:45.088
Ezra, get in here.

16:47.757 --> 16:49.384
Yeah?

16:49.384 --> 16:51.886
Where the hell is drawer 101,
Francis Scott?

16:51.886 --> 16:54.014
I don't know.
I didn't tag him.

16:54.014 --> 16:56.683
This isn't your handwriting?

16:56.683 --> 16:57.767
Nope.

17:01.354 --> 17:03.356
Sorry about the confusion.

17:03.356 --> 17:05.191
It's been a nightmare
around here.

17:05.191 --> 17:07.986
Bodies piling up every winter.
It's awful.

17:07.986 --> 17:11.656
But when he turns up,
I'll give you a call.

17:11.656 --> 17:12.991
You do that.

17:12.991 --> 17:15.618
Thanks.

17:15.618 --> 17:19.581
[drawer closes]

17:21.791 --> 17:22.959
[door closes]

17:22.959 --> 17:24.878
Hey, Ezra.

17:24.878 --> 17:28.631
You didn't tag Francis Scott?

17:28.631 --> 17:30.300
No.

17:31.926 --> 17:33.803
Interesting.

17:36.097 --> 17:38.850
Coroner's assistant, huh?

17:38.850 --> 17:42.896
That's, like,
one step above gassing puppies

17:42.896 --> 17:45.065
at the pound, no?

17:45.065 --> 17:46.775
[sighs]
I just can't even imagine

17:46.775 --> 17:49.444
all the creepy stuff
that happens in here.

17:49.444 --> 17:53.365
You probably don't want me
looking around here, right?

17:53.365 --> 17:56.534
You don't
intimidate me, lady.

17:56.534 --> 18:00.080
[drawer slams, Ezra screams]

18:00.080 --> 18:01.748
How about now?
[drawer slams]

18:01.748 --> 18:03.458
Jesus.

18:03.458 --> 18:05.919
Tell you what--I'll let you
keep doing whatever it is

18:05.919 --> 18:07.587
that you're doing down here

18:07.587 --> 18:10.674
if you tell me who came
and got Francis Scott's body.

18:10.674 --> 18:11.675
I don't know his name.

18:11.675 --> 18:13.259
He gets contraband
delivered here

18:13.259 --> 18:15.303
every once in a while
from overseas.

18:15.303 --> 18:16.346
I don't ask questions.

18:16.346 --> 18:18.014
[drawer slams]
Aah!

18:18.014 --> 18:19.599
This wasn't from overseas.

18:19.599 --> 18:22.060
Listen, they came in
flashing a bunch of cash,

18:22.060 --> 18:23.436
wanted the body cremated.

18:23.436 --> 18:26.356
That's a nice watch.

18:26.356 --> 18:28.108
- "They"?
- Yeah, yeah.

18:28.108 --> 18:29.901
Yeah, uh,
t-there were two of them.

18:29.901 --> 18:31.361
O-one I never seen before--

18:31.361 --> 18:34.322
t-t-the guy's brother, I guess,
fancy out-of-towner.

18:34.322 --> 18:36.908
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:36.908 --> 18:39.786
- What's his brother's name?
- I don't know.

18:39.786 --> 18:41.621
What do you know?

18:41.621 --> 18:44.207
They--they were driving
a green VW bus.

18:44.207 --> 18:46.668
Ah! I think they live
in C-Chinatown.

18:46.668 --> 18:49.754
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:49.754 --> 18:51.423
If you think
of anything else,

18:51.423 --> 18:53.383
you know where to find me.

18:53.383 --> 18:56.302
<i>[Bach's Cello Suite No. 1
playing]</i>

18:56.302 --> 19:02.267
♪ ♪

19:02.267 --> 19:04.227
Really a magnificent talent.

19:04.227 --> 19:07.647
Credit to you, sir,
discovering him.

19:07.647 --> 19:11.526
Well, in crisis, we're
all gluttons in our own way.

19:11.526 --> 19:13.862
You gorge yourself
on cellists, while I--

19:13.862 --> 19:17.782
well, I-I prefer
more traditional victuals.

19:17.782 --> 19:24.748
♪ ♪

19:27.792 --> 19:30.628
[music stops]

19:30.628 --> 19:32.505
If I knew you were coming,
I'd have rolled out the red--

19:32.505 --> 19:34.341
Oh, you
weren't expecting me...

19:34.341 --> 19:36.426
in the wake
of last night's events?

19:36.426 --> 19:38.303
And you eat--

19:38.303 --> 19:43.224
rather celebratory, considering
your slew of recent failures.

19:43.224 --> 19:45.935
- Comfort food, nothing more.
- Comfort?

19:45.935 --> 19:48.730
You think in history's
great tales of survival,

19:48.730 --> 19:51.191
legendary men who battled
their way back from defeat,

19:51.191 --> 19:52.984
they did so
by comforting themselves?

19:52.984 --> 19:54.235
Well, I'm merely suggesting--

19:54.235 --> 19:56.279
Or was it the threat
of starvation,

19:56.279 --> 19:58.365
the inevitable raping and pillaging,

19:58.365 --> 20:00.033
the eradication
of their bloodline

20:00.033 --> 20:01.242
that motivated these men

20:01.242 --> 20:03.453
to pull themselves back
from the fire?

20:07.248 --> 20:10.210
<i>[dark music]</i>

20:10.210 --> 20:17.384
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:18.343 --> 20:20.929
[chewing]

20:20.929 --> 20:25.392
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:25.392 --> 20:27.310
You know, it's understandable.

20:27.310 --> 20:29.104
People who are born
into wealth as you were--

20:29.104 --> 20:32.065
they often seek comfort
in the face of adversity.

20:32.065 --> 20:35.193
Perhaps it's time for you
to feel uncomfortable.

20:35.193 --> 20:36.736
Yeah?

20:36.736 --> 20:39.489
I mean, discomfort
is the great equalizer.

20:39.489 --> 20:41.408
Because the mess
your people made last night

20:41.408 --> 20:43.118
has brought
the missing coin press

20:43.118 --> 20:44.703
to the attention
of the High Table.

20:44.703 --> 20:46.538
I'll find it.
I got people in the field--

20:46.538 --> 20:48.331
You're a shell of yourself.

20:48.331 --> 20:50.917
Your own people
are stealing from you.

20:50.917 --> 20:52.627
I want
the High Table's resources.

20:52.627 --> 20:54.421
You have three days.

20:54.421 --> 20:56.381
You have three days
to locate the coin press

20:56.381 --> 20:58.591
and bring those responsible
to our feet.

20:58.591 --> 21:01.636
If you fail, the High Table
will declare interregnum,

21:01.636 --> 21:04.472
suspend your position
until we can name a successor.

21:04.472 --> 21:07.142
Your gilded cage
will come crashing in on you.

21:07.142 --> 21:09.811
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:09.811 --> 21:11.271
Enjoy your meal.

21:11.271 --> 21:13.898
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:13.898 --> 21:15.900
