<i>♪ But I guess
that's just the way ♪</i>

33:36.850 --> 33:40.395
<i>♪ The story goes ♪</i>

33:40.395 --> 33:42.981
<i>♪ You always smile but in-- ♪</i>

33:42.981 --> 33:46.151
[distant pounding]

33:46.151 --> 33:49.112
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

33:49.112 --> 33:52.866
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:52.866 --> 33:55.869
[distant clattering]

33:55.869 --> 34:02.125
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:02.125 --> 34:04.794
Check over there.

34:04.794 --> 34:06.880
What the hell?

34:06.880 --> 34:09.466
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:09.466 --> 34:11.551
[chuckles]

34:11.551 --> 34:13.720
No, fuck you.

34:13.720 --> 34:15.680
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:15.680 --> 34:19.309
<i>all: * Let's all go
to the lobby ♪</i>

34:19.309 --> 34:21.311
Spread out.

34:21.311 --> 34:24.397
<i>all: * Let's all go
to the lobby ♪</i>

34:24.397 --> 34:27.817
<i>♪ To get ourselves a treat ♪</i>

34:27.817 --> 34:30.153
<i>Little thing to eat.</i>

34:30.153 --> 34:32.697
<i>The popcorn can't be beat.</i>

34:32.697 --> 34:36.576
<i>all: * Let's all go
to the lobby ♪</i>

34:36.576 --> 34:39.454
<i>♪ To get ourselves a treat ♪</i>

34:39.454 --> 34:42.165
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

34:42.165 --> 34:46.002
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:46.002 --> 34:48.755
[gun cocks, gunshot]

34:48.755 --> 34:52.050
<i>♪ Can't live ♪</i>

34:52.050 --> 34:55.929
<i>♪ If living is without you ♪</i>

34:55.929 --> 34:59.391
<i>♪ Can't live ♪</i>

34:59.391 --> 35:02.977
<i>♪ I can't give anymore ♪</i>

35:02.977 --> 35:07.315
<i>♪ I can't live ♪</i>

35:07.315 --> 35:10.902
<i>♪ If living is without you ♪</i>

35:10.902 --> 35:14.114
<i>♪ I can't live ♪</i>

35:14.114 --> 35:19.828
<i>♪ I can't give anymore ♪</i>

35:19.828 --> 35:22.122
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:22.122 --> 35:25.208
<i>♪ If living is without you ♪</i>

35:25.208 --> 35:26.793
[grunts loudly]

35:26.793 --> 35:28.837
[music stops]

35:28.837 --> 35:32.048
[breathing heavily]

35:32.048 --> 35:35.260
<i>The men who come to me
are usually looking for help</i>

35:35.260 --> 35:37.595
<i>in some way or another.</i>

35:37.595 --> 35:40.015
After your brother
stole the coin press

35:40.015 --> 35:42.392
and you blew into town,

35:42.392 --> 35:44.477
I thought there was
a decent chance

35:44.477 --> 35:46.312
you'd walk through my door.

35:46.312 --> 35:49.190
My condolences, by the way.

35:49.190 --> 35:51.651
What do you know
about me, Winston?

35:51.651 --> 35:54.279
Well, people say
you have an army.

35:54.279 --> 35:56.239
And unlike every other player
in this town,

35:56.239 --> 35:58.867
you are not
under Cormac's thumb.

35:58.867 --> 36:01.077
Now I just need to know--
what is your going rate,

36:01.077 --> 36:02.495
and how soon can you start?

36:02.495 --> 36:04.205
I thought you'd be
smart enough

36:04.205 --> 36:06.708
to know
that I don't deal in dollars.

36:06.708 --> 36:09.544
It's how I maintain independence

36:09.544 --> 36:11.546
from men like Cormac.

36:11.546 --> 36:14.299
All right,
well, I'm very resourceful.

36:14.299 --> 36:15.508
Tell me what you need.

36:17.302 --> 36:19.095
Love.

36:19.095 --> 36:20.347
Love?

36:20.347 --> 36:22.182
The men I call my flock--

36:22.182 --> 36:26.269
you walk by them on the street
every day, never noticing,

36:26.269 --> 36:28.396
invisible...

36:28.396 --> 36:30.648
no self-worth.

36:30.648 --> 36:32.692
But you take those same men

36:32.692 --> 36:35.445
and give them back
their humanity,

36:35.445 --> 36:37.280
do you know what they give you
in return?

36:37.280 --> 36:39.157
What's that?

36:39.157 --> 36:41.785
Everything.

36:41.785 --> 36:45.205
And now
that same invisibility...

36:45.205 --> 36:47.707
they embrace it...

36:47.707 --> 36:51.878
because they no longer need you
to see them because...

36:51.878 --> 36:53.588
They see themselves.

36:53.588 --> 36:55.548
Love.

36:55.548 --> 36:59.219
- Can you dig it?
- [chuckles]

36:59.219 --> 37:01.554
I was born from rich folks.

37:01.554 --> 37:04.224
Didn't want their money.
Don't want yours.

37:04.224 --> 37:06.267
When a man comes
to needing help,

37:06.267 --> 37:10.397
I only have one requirement.

37:10.397 --> 37:12.232
They had to tell me
their story.

37:12.232 --> 37:15.235
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

37:15.235 --> 37:20.407
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:20.407 --> 37:22.826
I'm the man who's going
to kill Cormac O'Connor.

37:22.826 --> 37:26.204
No.

37:26.204 --> 37:28.123
It's too easy.

37:28.123 --> 37:30.417
Why are you the man

37:30.417 --> 37:33.378
who's going to kill
Cormac O'Connor?

37:33.378 --> 37:39.426
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:39.426 --> 37:42.429
[whispering indistinctly]

37:42.429 --> 37:44.931
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:44.931 --> 37:48.601
Your coming here wasn't just
predictable to me apparently.

37:48.601 --> 37:51.479
[tires squealing]
<i>It's being taken care of.</i>

37:51.479 --> 37:54.816
[tires screeching,
person mutters angrily]

37:57.152 --> 38:00.530
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:00.530 --> 38:03.616
[tires squealing]

38:03.616 --> 38:06.036
Time for you to go.

38:06.036 --> 38:08.663
Well, you--you still haven't
told me your price, yet.

38:08.663 --> 38:10.707
There's got to be something.

38:10.707 --> 38:12.917
Tough to buy for, aren't I?

38:14.544 --> 38:17.047
You'll be leaving
a different way.

38:17.047 --> 38:20.133
<i>[Pink Floyd's
"Welcome to the Machine"]</i>

38:20.133 --> 38:22.469
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:22.469 --> 38:25.889
<i>♪ Welcome, my son ♪</i>

38:25.889 --> 38:30.935
<i>♪ Welcome to the machine ♪</i>

38:30.935 --> 38:36.816
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:36.816 --> 38:39.569
<i>♪ Where have you been? ♪</i>

38:39.569 --> 38:41.154
He'll be right down.

38:41.154 --> 38:44.949
<i>♪ It's all right,
we know where you've been ♪</i>

38:44.949 --> 38:50.830
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:50.830 --> 38:55.168
<i>♪ You've been in the pipeline,
filling in time ♪</i>

38:55.168 --> 38:57.921
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:57.921 --> 39:02.592
<i>♪ Provided with toys
and scouting for boys ♪</i>

39:02.592 --> 39:05.303
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:05.303 --> 39:09.599
<i>♪ You bought a guitar
to punish your ma ♪</i>

39:09.599 --> 39:12.352
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:12.352 --> 39:15.105
<i>♪ You didn't like school ♪</i>

39:15.105 --> 39:20.985
<i>♪ And you know
you're nobody's fool ♪</i>

39:20.985 --> 39:24.072
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:24.072 --> 39:30.203
<i>♪ So welcome ♪</i>

39:30.203 --> 39:35.709
<i>♪ To the machine ♪</i>

39:35.709 --> 39:38.837
The Almighty made
the world in six days

39:38.837 --> 39:41.881
and rested on the seventh.

39:41.881 --> 39:44.718
The High Table have given us
three days

39:44.718 --> 39:47.137
and not a single minute
of rest.

39:48.596 --> 39:51.433
Know that if I go down...

39:51.433 --> 39:53.977
I'm taking all of you
down with me.

39:53.977 --> 39:55.687
You understand?

39:55.687 --> 39:57.981
Your failure humiliates me,

39:57.981 --> 40:01.985
and it's no secret what I do
to those who humiliate me.

40:01.985 --> 40:04.237
Now get out of here
so I can pray.

40:04.237 --> 40:05.613
It's a sacrilege,

40:05.613 --> 40:07.615
you people even being here
in the first place.

40:07.615 --> 40:10.035
It's a wonder you don't
all burst into flames.

40:10.035 --> 40:17.000
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:18.501 --> 40:19.669
Help me.

40:19.669 --> 40:26.843
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:26.843 --> 40:28.720
Help me.

40:28.720 --> 40:32.432
I wish
I had the answers, sir.

40:32.432 --> 40:34.517
I wasn't talking to you.

40:34.517 --> 40:41.691
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:10.345 --> 41:12.472
[yelling]

41:12.472 --> 41:13.807
Jesus!

41:13.807 --> 41:16.476
Oh.
Jesus Christ.

41:16.476 --> 41:18.645
Oh, Winston, sorry.

41:18.645 --> 41:20.897
Simple hello next time, please.

41:22.691 --> 41:24.651
What the hell happened here?

41:24.651 --> 41:27.487
Whatever Frankie took,
he didn't give it back.

41:27.487 --> 41:30.782
Those fuckers tore this place
apart looking for it.

41:30.782 --> 41:32.742
I've been hiding all day.

41:35.662 --> 41:37.580
Sorry about your brother.

41:37.580 --> 41:39.582
It's not an easy life.

41:41.376 --> 41:43.878
- Have you heard from Charlie?
- Hell, no.

41:43.878 --> 41:46.423
Bailed as soon as things
heated up, typical Charlie.

41:46.423 --> 41:48.591
That asshole still owes me
money for the helicopter ride.

41:48.591 --> 41:50.260
Of course he does.

41:50.260 --> 41:51.344
So I snagged his Mustang

41:51.344 --> 41:53.304
and a few other items
worth something.

41:53.304 --> 41:55.640
I got a kid to feed.

41:55.640 --> 41:57.559
- You good?
- Mm-hmm.

41:57.559 --> 41:59.519
Hey, you all right, chap?

41:59.519 --> 42:00.729
I'm good.

42:00.729 --> 42:02.731
Figured you'd be
long gone by now.

42:02.731 --> 42:05.358
What do you need from Charlie?

42:05.358 --> 42:06.901
I'm putting a team together,

42:06.901 --> 42:09.195
and he's always told me that
he has a guy for everything.

42:09.195 --> 42:11.197
Yeah, I'm the guy.

42:12.490 --> 42:13.700
Jesus.

42:13.700 --> 42:15.702
So let me get this right.

42:15.702 --> 42:17.912
You won't even touch a gun,

42:17.912 --> 42:20.707
but all this other crazy
lethal shit, that's fine?

42:20.707 --> 42:23.835
It was my father's code,
Lemmy--no guns.

42:23.835 --> 42:25.962
I helped build this place.

42:25.962 --> 42:28.590
Wouldn't make sense
for me to live any other way.

42:28.590 --> 42:31.676
With hand-to-hand
or any other weapon,

42:31.676 --> 42:35.597
you have a choice--
life or death.

42:35.597 --> 42:39.642
With a gun, there is
no choice...

42:39.642 --> 42:40.977
only death.

42:45.523 --> 42:48.193
You want me to--
All right.

42:48.193 --> 42:49.986
Come on, switch.

42:52.447 --> 42:53.615
[clears throat]

42:53.615 --> 42:55.200
Why are you doing this,
Lemmy?

42:55.200 --> 42:57.494
'Cause you scare
the shit out of me.

42:57.494 --> 43:00.246
No, this suicide mission.

43:00.246 --> 43:02.165
You didn't love Frankie.

43:04.459 --> 43:06.836
No, but I love Miles.

43:08.546 --> 43:10.006
I know.

43:10.006 --> 43:12.884
I mean, look at everything
he gave me, you know?

43:12.884 --> 43:16.721
I work there, eat there...

43:16.721 --> 43:19.432
sleep right there.

43:19.432 --> 43:21.851
This is my foxhole now.

43:21.851 --> 43:23.728
After the war,

43:23.728 --> 43:26.856
if it wasn't for Miles...

43:26.856 --> 43:29.067
I would have...

43:29.067 --> 43:31.778
I know.

43:31.778 --> 43:33.655
Queenpin--
it's an understatement.

43:33.655 --> 43:35.532
I'm not exactly sure
what it is I saw,

43:35.532 --> 43:39.411
but all I know is we need her
and her entire operation.

43:39.411 --> 43:41.121
How much is it gonna cost?

43:41.121 --> 43:44.124
Well, she's not interested
in money apparently, just love.

43:44.124 --> 43:48.211
A deadly hippie--
now, there's an oxymoron.

43:48.211 --> 43:49.879
Uh-oh.

43:49.879 --> 43:52.298
What's this?

43:53.633 --> 43:55.844
Whoa, lookee here.

43:55.844 --> 43:58.304
Did Frankie make this?

43:58.304 --> 43:59.889
Thank you, Yen.

43:59.889 --> 44:03.643
<i>♪ ♪</i>

44:03.643 --> 44:05.520
You think this means
she's on board?

44:05.520 --> 44:06.771
Fingers crossed.

44:06.771 --> 44:08.773
- Gene.
- Hmm?

44:08.773 --> 44:10.900
This track
with what you remember?

44:10.900 --> 44:12.527
Frankie did a good job,

44:12.527 --> 44:15.822
but it's a sketch,
not a blueprint.

44:15.822 --> 44:17.490
There's everything in that building,

44:17.490 --> 44:20.368
from secret doors
to Cormac's bulletproof glass

44:20.368 --> 44:23.413
to who knows what else
he's got in there now.

44:24.914 --> 44:26.374
Right there.

44:26.374 --> 44:28.668
- The armory.
- That's your Holy Grail.

44:28.668 --> 44:31.129
Holy Grail for who?

44:31.129 --> 44:33.423
Whoever gets to it first.

44:33.423 --> 44:37.719
Why does a hotel for hit men
have an armory, anyway?

44:37.719 --> 44:40.180
Crooks are always worried
somebody gonna come after them,

44:40.180 --> 44:42.640
whether it's cops
or some other crook.

44:42.640 --> 44:46.269
So the, uh, armory helps them
get a good night's sleep.

44:46.269 --> 44:49.022
- We need an inside man.
- Hmm.

44:49.022 --> 44:51.733
In the old days, maybe, but...

44:51.733 --> 44:54.694
now there's two kind
of folk in there--

44:54.694 --> 44:56.196
too evil to be trusted

44:56.196 --> 44:58.948
or too brainwashed
to betray Cormac.

44:58.948 --> 45:01.701
It's not a frickin' club
anymore--it's a cult.

45:01.701 --> 45:03.536
There's got to be
an Achilles' heel

45:03.536 --> 45:04.788
in there somewhere.

45:04.788 --> 45:07.040
Well, while you look into it,

45:07.040 --> 45:09.209
I can't be late
for this pickup.

45:14.297 --> 45:17.342
<i>[Bobbie Gentry's
"Seasons Come, Seasons Go"]</i>

45:17.342 --> 45:19.803
<i>♪ ♪</i>

45:19.803 --> 45:23.723
Left hand, red.

45:23.723 --> 45:26.017
[laughter]
That's a stretch.

45:26.017 --> 45:28.395
You're doing good.

45:28.395 --> 45:30.397
Again, right hand, red.

45:30.397 --> 45:32.565
- [knock at door]
- Right hand, red.

45:32.565 --> 45:36.903
[indistinct chatter]

45:36.903 --> 45:39.698
Who invited
somebody over here, huh?

45:39.698 --> 45:45.870
<i>♪ ♪</i>

45:45.870 --> 45:47.789
Jesus.

45:47.789 --> 45:50.834
You're full of surprises
lately, aren't you?

45:50.834 --> 45:52.585
I need a favor.

45:52.585 --> 45:56.923
Hon, is that KD?
Why don't you come in and play?

45:56.923 --> 45:58.967
Yeah, you know what?
I would love to.

45:58.967 --> 46:00.427
She can't tonight,
sweetheart--she's working.

46:00.427 --> 46:03.263
Another time.
Just give me one minute.

46:03.263 --> 46:05.223
You need a favor?

46:05.223 --> 46:07.267
Anything to do
with that phone call?

46:07.267 --> 46:08.601
Yeah, it does.

46:08.601 --> 46:11.271
[indistinct happy shouting]

46:11.271 --> 46:13.606
- God damn, you smell good.
- All right.

46:13.606 --> 46:15.567
Your wife is 30 feet away.

46:15.567 --> 46:17.235
Yeah, I know where she is.
Just keep your voice down.

46:17.235 --> 46:18.862
Yeah, well, are you
gonna help me or what?

46:18.862 --> 46:22.115
Depends on what you want.
[indistinct chatter continues]

46:22.115 --> 46:25.076
I need to find a green VW bus
in Chinatown.

46:25.076 --> 46:28.038
- Without a warrant?
- Yeah, without a warrant.

46:29.497 --> 46:31.916
Well, I'm sorry,
but it's a little arousing,

46:31.916 --> 46:34.711
you trying to bend the rules
all of a sudden.

46:34.711 --> 46:36.880
You know what?

46:36.880 --> 46:38.631
I never had
a family game night.

46:38.631 --> 46:40.133
Twister looks real fun.

46:40.133 --> 46:44.679
All right, all right,
all right, I'm gonna help you.

46:44.679 --> 46:46.514
It was nice seeing you, Janice.

46:46.514 --> 46:49.476
- Maybe next time, all right?
- Okay, you too.

46:49.476 --> 46:52.604
Oh, my goodness.
[indistinct chatter continues]

46:52.604 --> 46:56.399
<i>♪ Leaving me to stay
and face December snow ♪</i>

46:56.399 --> 46:58.360
Fuck.

46:58.360 --> 47:02.072
<i>♪ The seasons come... ♪</i>

47:34.688 --> 47:36.272
Okay?

47:46.241 --> 47:49.452
Fight of the century?

47:49.452 --> 47:51.454
No.

47:51.454 --> 47:55.083
His real fight of the century
was against going to Vietnam.

47:56.543 --> 47:58.628
The government tried to destroy him,

47:58.628 --> 48:00.046
refused to let them box,

48:00.046 --> 48:02.382
ordered him
to do five years in jail,

48:02.382 --> 48:06.594
but he fought that
at the peak of his career...

48:06.594 --> 48:09.723
went all the way
to the Supreme Court and won.

48:09.723 --> 48:13.226
No jail time, no Nam.

48:20.525 --> 48:22.610
Yeah.

48:22.610 --> 48:23.862
But to me and Frankie,

48:23.862 --> 48:26.740
it's what we called
the loudest day of war.

48:26.740 --> 48:31.077
I mean, there was
20-millimeter cannon fire...

48:31.077 --> 48:34.622
helicopter gunships,
B-52 payloads.

48:34.622 --> 48:37.542
You couldn't hear
the guy next to you.

48:37.542 --> 48:39.753
And what was left of our unit
was caught right in the middle,

48:39.753 --> 48:44.758
nowhere to run,
no radio, enemy advancing.

48:44.758 --> 48:48.178
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

48:48.178 --> 48:51.431
All you could do was pray.

48:51.431 --> 48:54.684
And we did for what
must have been hours.

48:56.603 --> 48:58.772
But at some point,
I realized I could hear Frankie

48:58.772 --> 49:01.566
talking to God...

49:01.566 --> 49:03.568
no bombs...

49:03.568 --> 49:05.570
no helicopters...

49:05.570 --> 49:08.198
total silence.

49:09.824 --> 49:13.953
It was the weirdest feeling...

49:13.953 --> 49:15.955
like the war suddenly ended,

49:15.955 --> 49:19.125
but they'd forgotten
to tell us.

49:19.125 --> 49:22.796
So, when we got back to base...

49:22.796 --> 49:27.133
we realized the war
had stopped because...

49:27.133 --> 49:30.345
being broadcast
all over the world,

49:30.345 --> 49:32.347
Muhammad Ali
was fighting Joe Frazier

49:32.347 --> 49:34.224
at Madison Square Garden.

49:34.224 --> 49:36.351
<i>♪ ♪</i>

49:36.351 --> 49:38.311
Both sides had stopped
killing each other

49:38.311 --> 49:39.979
just long enough to listen.

49:39.979 --> 49:46.986
<i>♪ ♪</i>

49:46.986 --> 49:49.823
Frankie and I...

49:49.823 --> 49:53.201
sat over that radio...

49:53.201 --> 49:55.286
and shared something
I don't think either of us

49:55.286 --> 49:57.247
had ever experienced...

49:58.665 --> 50:00.834
[inhales sharply]

50:00.834 --> 50:03.795
A true moment of peace...

50:03.795 --> 50:07.257
'cause on both sides,
there was no enemy.

50:07.257 --> 50:14.431
<i>♪ ♪</i>

50:42.042 --> 50:44.294
[lights thud]

50:44.294 --> 50:45.712
That's the signal.

50:45.712 --> 50:48.131
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

50:48.131 --> 50:52.260
<i>♪ ♪</i>

50:52.260 --> 50:55.263
If anything happens,
just leave without me.

50:55.263 --> 51:02.437
<i>♪ ♪</i>

51:21.206 --> 51:23.291
[van door closes,
engine turning over]

51:23.291 --> 51:28.171
<i>♪ ♪</i>

51:28.171 --> 51:30.924
[tires squealing]

51:30.924 --> 51:36.179
<i>♪ ♪</i>

51:36.179 --> 51:39.057
[number pad beeping]

51:39.057 --> 51:42.769
[buzzer sounds]

51:42.769 --> 51:45.355
[number pad beeping]

51:45.355 --> 51:48.525
[buzzer sounds]

51:48.525 --> 51:50.110
Shit.

51:50.110 --> 51:52.612
- [dog barking]
- Hey.

51:52.612 --> 51:55.615
What's going on?
We have an outage?

51:55.615 --> 51:57.367
Uh, yep.

51:57.367 --> 51:59.619
Nobody on the radio
called it in.

51:59.619 --> 52:01.287
Oh.

52:01.287 --> 52:02.997
That's weird.
You sure?

52:02.997 --> 52:04.541
[dog snarls]

52:04.541 --> 52:08.169
Can you step
out of the vehicle?

52:08.169 --> 52:10.255
[tires squealing,
engine revving]

52:10.255 --> 52:12.632
Hey! Hey, hey, hey!
[dog barking]

52:12.632 --> 52:15.135
Shit plan!

52:15.135 --> 52:16.469
Hey!

52:16.469 --> 52:18.555
Hey, whoa!
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!

52:18.555 --> 52:20.724
Hey! Hey!

52:20.724 --> 52:22.684
No, stop!

52:22.684 --> 52:25.729
<i>[elegant cello music playing]</i>

52:25.729 --> 52:30.400
♪ ♪

52:30.400 --> 52:32.485
[music stops]

52:32.485 --> 52:35.113
Always the best part
of my day.

52:35.113 --> 52:37.323
You flatter me, Charon.

52:37.323 --> 52:39.868
- Writing to your father again?
- Yes.

52:39.868 --> 52:43.079
I was just telling him
how brilliant you are.

52:43.079 --> 52:45.999
<i>I'm sure I'm not
as talented as he is.</i>

52:45.999 --> 52:49.002
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

52:49.002 --> 52:55.925
<i>♪ ♪</i>

52:57.552 --> 52:59.346
That building right there--

52:59.346 --> 53:01.681
that's where I can do
the most damage.

53:01.681 --> 53:06.311
<i>♪ ♪</i>

53:06.311 --> 53:07.854
Looks like apartments.

53:07.854 --> 53:10.190
What are the odds we can find
a vacant one?

53:10.190 --> 53:12.776
You leave that to me.
I'm your guy on the outside.

53:12.776 --> 53:15.695
Worry about your guys
on the inside.

53:15.695 --> 53:17.072
<i>You ever think of leaving?</i>

53:17.072 --> 53:20.116
<i>♪ ♪</i>

53:20.116 --> 53:22.702
- The hotel?
- Yeah.

53:22.702 --> 53:26.289
There's so much
to experience out there.

53:26.289 --> 53:27.957
True.

53:27.957 --> 53:31.169
But I don't think Mr. O'Connor
can survive without me.

53:31.169 --> 53:33.338
<i>♪ ♪</i>

53:33.338 --> 53:35.173
Or you without him.

53:35.173 --> 53:39.928
<i>♪ ♪</i>

53:39.928 --> 53:42.555
Does your father know
about this place?

53:42.555 --> 53:44.766
Yes, of course.
I've told him.

53:44.766 --> 53:47.060
<i>♪ ♪</i>

53:47.060 --> 53:48.311
Have you really told him?

53:48.311 --> 53:51.272
<i>♪ ♪</i>

53:51.272 --> 53:53.483
Do you know
what goes on here?

53:55.110 --> 53:56.236
I've heard rumors.

53:56.236 --> 53:57.737
When I left my country,

53:57.737 --> 54:00.156
my father gave me
everything he had saved

54:00.156 --> 54:03.743
so I could come to the U.S.--
a fresh start he never had.

54:03.743 --> 54:05.912
I sent him a photo
of me standing right here

54:05.912 --> 54:07.205
with a view of the city.

54:07.205 --> 54:08.915
And guess what.

54:08.915 --> 54:10.709
He cried...

54:10.709 --> 54:14.087
tears of joy for my success.

54:14.087 --> 54:15.630
You must understand--

54:15.630 --> 54:18.341
where I'm from,
violence is rampant.

54:18.341 --> 54:21.052
Here at least the chaos
is controlled.

54:21.052 --> 54:24.222
I feel safer here
than I ever did back home.

54:24.222 --> 54:28.560
<i>♪ ♪</i>

54:28.560 --> 54:30.437
I can't imagine.

54:30.437 --> 54:32.564
- You remember that red light?
- Yes.

54:32.564 --> 54:34.274
Cormac mash that button,

54:34.274 --> 54:35.608
red light comes on
in every room,

54:35.608 --> 54:38.403
including the shitter,
and voilà...

54:38.403 --> 54:40.864
killing on hotel
grounds is allowed,

54:40.864 --> 54:42.991
and our whole goddamn plan
is over before it started.

54:42.991 --> 54:44.325
If we do it right,

54:44.325 --> 54:46.953
Cormac's dead before he
can mash that red button.

54:46.953 --> 54:48.455
And by the time the rest

54:48.455 --> 54:50.999
of that godforsaken place
knows he's dead, it's too late.

54:50.999 --> 54:53.752
We'll have the undeniable
tactical advantage.

54:53.752 --> 54:55.628
Okay.

54:55.628 --> 54:58.548
How exactly do we get to Cormac

54:58.548 --> 55:01.968
so as to attain that
undeniable tactical advantage?

55:01.968 --> 55:04.137
You said
there were two types of people

55:04.137 --> 55:05.680
in The Continental, right?

55:05.680 --> 55:07.724
Evil and brainwashed.

55:07.724 --> 55:08.641
Why?

55:08.641 --> 55:10.393
Which one's which?

55:10.393 --> 55:17.442
<i>♪ ♪</i>

55:17.442 --> 55:20.653
Well, aren't you smart.

55:20.653 --> 55:22.655
I wanted to tell you-
I've been accepted

55:22.655 --> 55:24.699
to a music conservatory
in Ireland.

55:24.699 --> 55:27.494
I'll soon be leaving the city.

55:27.494 --> 55:28.995
That will be good for you.

55:28.995 --> 55:31.831
<i>♪ ♪</i>

55:31.831 --> 55:35.335
Perhaps you could come
with me.

55:35.335 --> 55:38.046
[scoffs]
I-I could never do that.

55:38.046 --> 55:39.339
Why not?

55:39.339 --> 55:41.007
When I first arrived,

55:41.007 --> 55:44.177
Mr. O'Connor promised
he would bring my father over

55:44.177 --> 55:46.638
once I'd proven myself.

55:46.638 --> 55:48.515
That time is soon.

55:48.515 --> 55:52.769
<i>♪ ♪</i>

55:52.769 --> 55:55.522
I hope he keeps his promise

55:55.522 --> 55:58.483
<i>The cellist is just
a hired hand,</i>

55:58.483 --> 56:00.527
<i>but the kid...</i>

56:00.527 --> 56:01.861
I don't know, Winston.

56:01.861 --> 56:06.074
Cormac's been grooming him
for some time.

56:06.074 --> 56:10.203
- It'd be high risk.
- Also high reward.

56:10.203 --> 56:17.127
<i>♪ ♪</i>

56:18.503 --> 56:21.464
[camera shutter clicking]

56:21.464 --> 56:26.094
<i>♪ ♪</i>

56:26.094 --> 56:28.596
<i>[upbeat rock music]</i>

56:28.596 --> 56:31.474
<i>[person singing
in native language]</i>

56:31.474 --> 56:38.648
<i>♪ ♪</i>

57:18.772 --> 57:20.648
Ha ha.
My man.

57:20.648 --> 57:22.776
- My brother.
- How you doing, man?

57:22.776 --> 57:24.986
- Any requests?
- Surprise me.

57:24.986 --> 57:27.238
Ah, right on, brother.
Right on.

57:27.238 --> 57:34.120
♪ ♪

57:34.120 --> 57:37.165
[music stops,
indistinct chatter]

57:39.125 --> 57:42.170
[Orgone's
"Funky Nassau" playing]

57:42.170 --> 57:47.258
♪ ♪

57:47.258 --> 57:50.637
♪ Nassau's gone funky ♪

57:50.637 --> 57:52.347
♪ Nassau's gone soul ♪

57:52.347 --> 57:55.266
♪ ♪

57:55.266 --> 57:57.977
♪ We've got
a doggone beat now ♪

57:57.977 --> 58:01.648
♪ We're gonna call
our very own ♪

58:01.648 --> 58:04.943
Charon?
You good?

58:04.943 --> 58:08.029
Yes.
Thank you, Jamal.

58:08.029 --> 58:10.699
I have no idea what
to write in response.

58:10.699 --> 58:12.283
Words fail me.

58:12.283 --> 58:15.328
♪ ♪

58:15.328 --> 58:18.164
Trouble back home?

58:18.164 --> 58:21.251
Unfortunately, I think
if your shop were in my city,

58:21.251 --> 58:23.003
there would be no shop today.

58:23.003 --> 58:25.672
He seems to be coming
for everybody--

58:25.672 --> 58:27.298
senseless.

58:27.298 --> 58:31.386
♪ ♪

58:31.386 --> 58:34.347
Come over here a minute.
I got something for you.

58:34.347 --> 58:36.099
Take your mind off it.

58:37.892 --> 58:42.147
♪ Listen to the drummer
play his feet ♪

58:42.147 --> 58:45.358
♪ ♪

58:45.358 --> 58:47.569
♪ Listen to the bass man ♪

58:47.569 --> 58:50.155
♪ Go get
that same groovy beat ♪

58:50.155 --> 58:53.116
♪ ♪

58:53.116 --> 58:57.787
♪ Listen to the guitar
give that soul some, too ♪

58:57.787 --> 59:01.791
<i>♪ ♪</i>

59:01.791 --> 59:06.379
<i>♪ Come on, now,
bring it on home to you ♪</i>

59:06.379 --> 59:08.381
<i>♪ Play the funky now ♪</i>

59:08.381 --> 59:12.510
<i>♪ ♪</i>

59:12.510 --> 59:14.471
<i>♪ Oh, yeah ♪</i>

59:14.471 --> 59:16.181
<i>♪ Funky ♪</i>

59:16.181 --> 59:18.683
<i>♪ ♪</i>

59:18.683 --> 59:20.727
<i>♪ Funky Nassau ♪</i>

59:20.727 --> 59:22.979
<i>♪ Listen, listen good ♪</i>

59:24.773 --> 59:26.941
<i>♪ New York, you know ♪</i>

59:26.941 --> 59:30.403
<i>♪ Has got
a whole lot of soul ♪</i>

59:30.403 --> 59:32.405
<i>♪ Good God ♪</i>

59:32.405 --> 59:34.908
<i>♪ London Town ♪</i>

59:34.908 --> 59:38.828
<i>♪ Is too doggone cold ♪</i>

59:38.828 --> 59:40.622
<i>♪ Yeah ♪</i>

59:40.622 --> 59:42.832
<i>♪ Nassau's got sunshine ♪</i>

59:42.832 --> 59:46.586
Hey! Get over here!
[dog barking]

59:46.586 --> 59:48.755
<i>♪ Yeah ♪</i>

59:48.755 --> 59:50.757
<i>♪ But we've gone funky ♪</i>

59:50.757 --> 59:53.718
<i>♪ And we got some soul, too ♪</i>

59:53.718 --> 59:56.596
<i>♪ All right ♪</i>

59:56.596 --> 01:00:10.276
<i>♪ Funky Nassau ♪</i>

01:00:10.276 --> 01:00:11.319
<i>♪ Listen ♪</i>

01:00:11.319 --> 01:00:14.531
<i>♪ Funky Nassau ♪</i>

01:00:14.531 --> 01:00:16.491
<i>♪ Funky ♪</i>

01:00:16.491 --> 01:00:20.286
[indistinct chatter]

01:00:20.286 --> 01:00:22.455
Damn it!
Stop!

01:00:22.455 --> 01:00:29.379
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:00:29.379 --> 01:00:30.839
Come here, you little shit!

01:00:30.839 --> 01:00:32.590
Why you keep breaking
my windows, huh?

01:00:32.590 --> 01:00:34.551
Get your hands off him.

01:00:34.551 --> 01:00:36.678
Get in.

01:00:36.678 --> 01:00:38.304
Glass needs picking up.

01:00:38.304 --> 01:00:40.682
Either he does it,
or you do it.

01:00:42.934 --> 01:00:45.395
<i>[James Brown's
"Get Up Offa That Thing"]</i>

01:00:45.395 --> 01:00:46.896
<i>♪ Ow ♪</i>

01:00:46.896 --> 01:00:48.982
<i>♪ Oh, whoo ♪</i>

01:00:48.982 --> 01:00:50.483
<i>♪ Say it now ♪</i>

01:00:50.483 --> 01:00:57.407
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:00:59.034 --> 01:01:01.036
<i>♪ Get up offa that thing ♪</i>

01:01:01.036 --> 01:01:03.329
<i>♪ And dance
till you feel better ♪</i>

01:01:03.329 --> 01:01:06.332
<i>♪ Get up offa that thing
and dance till you ♪</i>

01:01:06.332 --> 01:01:07.667
<i>♪ Sing it now ♪</i>

01:01:07.667 --> 01:01:09.210
<i>♪ Get up offa that thing ♪</i>

01:01:09.210 --> 01:01:11.880
<i>♪ And dance
till you feel better ♪</i>

01:01:11.880 --> 01:01:13.298
<i>♪ Get up offa that thing ♪</i>

01:01:13.298 --> 01:01:15.675
<i>♪ And try to release
that pressure ♪</i>

01:01:15.675 --> 01:01:17.093
<i>♪ Get up offa that thing ♪</i>

01:01:17.093 --> 01:01:19.596
<i>♪ And dance
till you feel better ♪</i>

01:01:19.596 --> 01:01:21.681
<i>♪ Get up offa that thing ♪</i>

01:01:21.681 --> 01:01:23.725
<i>♪ Shake it, say it now ♪</i>

01:01:23.725 --> 01:01:25.226
<i>♪ Get up offa that thing ♪</i>

01:01:25.226 --> 01:01:27.604
<i>♪ And dance
till you feel better ♪</i>

01:01:27.604 --> 01:01:29.731
<i>♪ Get up offa that thing ♪</i>

01:01:29.731 --> 01:01:32.233
<i>♪ Try to release
that pressure ♪</i>

01:01:32.233 --> 01:01:35.862
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:01:35.862 --> 01:01:37.739
[gunshot, people screaming]

01:01:37.739 --> 01:01:39.449
You've embarrassed
them enough.

01:01:48.249 --> 01:01:51.294
[indistinct shouting
in native language]

01:01:53.546 --> 01:01:55.131
Please.

01:01:55.131 --> 01:01:57.217
[traditional
Chinese music plays]

01:01:59.761 --> 01:02:05.850
♪ ♪

01:02:05.850 --> 01:02:07.519
You own this place?

01:02:07.519 --> 01:02:10.271
Not the place,
just the people.

01:02:10.271 --> 01:02:12.857
Your chicken feet are coming.

01:02:12.857 --> 01:02:16.486
My Haitian grandma used to
mail chicken feet to her door,

01:02:16.486 --> 01:02:18.321
scare away the boogeyman.

01:02:26.454 --> 01:02:30.375
One-armed beggars
earn twice as much.

01:02:30.375 --> 01:02:32.085
Ironic, isn't it?

01:02:32.085 --> 01:02:34.379
Kid has the same problem
you have.

01:02:34.379 --> 01:02:35.922
Thinks he's special.

01:02:35.922 --> 01:02:38.133
Doesn't follow the rules.

01:02:38.133 --> 01:02:41.344
- I give him purpose.
- Throwing rocks at my dojo.

01:02:41.344 --> 01:02:43.763
"Dojo" is Japanese.
This is Chinatown.

01:02:43.763 --> 01:02:45.890
Daddy got away
with a lot of shit.

01:02:45.890 --> 01:02:47.809
- You know that?
- And that stops with you?

01:02:47.809 --> 01:02:49.352
<i>Kwoon.</i>

01:02:49.352 --> 01:02:51.938
All he had to do was use
the right word.

01:02:51.938 --> 01:02:53.606
<i>Kwoon.</i>

01:02:53.606 --> 01:02:55.108
See how easy that is?

01:02:55.108 --> 01:02:57.110
So you're harassing us
because we missed the mark

01:02:57.110 --> 01:02:59.279
on cultural specificity?

01:02:59.279 --> 01:03:01.990
You people had a free ride
for too long.

01:03:01.990 --> 01:03:04.159
And I don't give a shit
who your daddy was.

01:03:04.159 --> 01:03:06.202
"You people"?
Why don't you admit it?

01:03:06.202 --> 01:03:07.328
You hate that he won the belts.

01:03:07.328 --> 01:03:09.289
You hate
that he won the hearts.

01:03:09.289 --> 01:03:11.332
You can't stand any of that
because he was Black.

01:03:11.332 --> 01:03:12.917
And you want to keep
telling yourself

01:03:12.917 --> 01:03:14.085
that we stole something,

01:03:14.085 --> 01:03:15.795
that we didn't come
by it honestly

01:03:15.795 --> 01:03:17.255
because we don't look like you.

01:03:17.255 --> 01:03:19.257
Well, my father
built that place

01:03:19.257 --> 01:03:23.345
by beating the best of the best
and living a life of honor.

01:03:23.345 --> 01:03:26.181
So much more to this story
than you know.

01:03:26.181 --> 01:03:29.934
You're the thief
in this hood, the parasite.

01:03:29.934 --> 01:03:31.644
<i>♪ Gow! ♪</i>

01:03:31.644 --> 01:03:33.438
<i>[Tom Waits'</i>

01:03:33.438 --> 01:03:35.982
<i>"A Sweet Little Bullet
from a Pretty Blue Gun"]</i>

01:03:35.982 --> 01:03:38.401
Nail those chicken feet
to that door.

01:03:41.029 --> 01:03:43.490
<i>♪ Well, it's raining ♪</i>

01:03:43.490 --> 01:03:45.992
<i>♪ It's pouring ♪</i>

01:03:45.992 --> 01:03:50.330
<i>♪ Didn't bring a sweater ♪</i>

01:03:50.330 --> 01:03:53.833
<i>♪ Nebraska
will never let you ♪</i>

01:03:53.833 --> 01:03:56.670
<i>♪ Come back home ♪</i>

01:03:56.670 --> 01:03:59.506
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:03:59.506 --> 01:04:03.176
<i>♪ No, that ain't
no cherry bomb ♪</i>

01:04:03.176 --> 01:04:06.680
<i>♪ Fourth of July's all done ♪</i>

01:04:06.680 --> 01:04:08.348
[dog barking]

01:04:08.348 --> 01:04:11.518
<i>♪ It's just some fool
playing that second line ♪</i>

01:04:11.518 --> 01:04:14.938
<i>♪ From the barrel
of a pretty blue gun ♪</i>

01:04:14.938 --> 01:04:18.108
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:04:18.108 --> 01:04:20.485
Guess we're
giving up smoking.

01:04:20.485 --> 01:04:27.450
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:04:29.619 --> 01:04:32.831
The, uh, trials of a
small-business owner,

01:04:32.831 --> 01:04:35.208
huh, Lou-Lou?

01:04:35.208 --> 01:04:36.668
I didn't know
that you had a room

01:04:36.668 --> 01:04:39.337
at The Continental, Gene.

01:04:39.337 --> 01:04:41.923
Well, most folks
don't like to tell

01:04:41.923 --> 01:04:43.550
every little old thing.

01:04:43.550 --> 01:04:46.136
Is there anything else
my brother knows that I don't?

01:04:47.220 --> 01:04:49.389
That's hard to say.

01:04:49.389 --> 01:04:52.350
You'd, uh--
you'd have to ask him.

01:04:52.350 --> 01:04:54.894
Excuse me.

01:04:54.894 --> 01:04:57.647
What you got there,
Mr. Postman?

01:04:57.647 --> 01:05:00.150
Our tactical advantage.

01:05:00.150 --> 01:05:03.153
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

01:05:03.153 --> 01:05:07.615
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:05:07.615 --> 01:05:10.577
[indistinct chatter]

01:05:16.124 --> 01:05:17.876
This bus is out of service.

01:05:17.876 --> 01:05:20.337
- You understand me?
- Understood.

01:05:25.050 --> 01:05:28.094
Everyone out.
Bus service has stopped.

01:05:28.094 --> 01:05:29.804
You serious?

01:05:29.804 --> 01:05:31.598
- I've got places to be.
- Move!

01:05:31.598 --> 01:05:33.183
You heard the lady.

01:05:35.477 --> 01:05:37.437
Not you.

01:05:37.437 --> 01:05:39.230
Take a seat.

01:05:39.230 --> 01:05:42.400
[light music playing]

01:05:42.400 --> 01:05:49.366
♪ ♪

01:05:56.706 --> 01:05:59.542
[clears throat]
You asked to see me, sir?

01:06:03.171 --> 01:06:05.382
[golf ball clatters,
glass clinks]

01:06:05.382 --> 01:06:08.551
They told you I've accepted
an opportunity elsewhere?

01:06:08.551 --> 01:06:11.012
The conservatory.

01:06:11.012 --> 01:06:13.431
I heard.

01:06:13.431 --> 01:06:15.517
Congratulations.

01:06:15.517 --> 01:06:16.810
Thank you.

01:06:16.810 --> 01:06:18.269
It's rare in this environment

01:06:18.269 --> 01:06:20.730
to find anyone who's interested
in higher education.

01:06:22.691 --> 01:06:24.150
I want you to know

01:06:24.150 --> 01:06:27.070
how much I've appreciated
my time here,

01:06:27.070 --> 01:06:29.072
however brief.

01:06:31.908 --> 01:06:33.618
They, uh, told me
to bring this.

01:06:33.618 --> 01:06:36.579
Did you want me
to play something for you?

01:06:36.579 --> 01:06:37.997
[chuckles]

01:06:37.997 --> 01:06:40.125
Tell me about your new school.

01:06:40.125 --> 01:06:42.168
Is it the Canterbury...

01:06:42.168 --> 01:06:45.296
up on the hillside
overlooking Cork?

01:06:45.296 --> 01:06:46.965
It is.
How did--

01:06:46.965 --> 01:06:48.842
I made a few calls.

01:06:48.842 --> 01:06:51.052
Okay, one call.

01:06:51.052 --> 01:06:53.138
I vouched for your potential.

01:06:53.138 --> 01:06:55.306
<i>[ominous music]</i>

01:06:55.306 --> 01:06:57.517
T-thank you, again, sir.

01:06:57.517 --> 01:07:00.395
The reach of my influence
surprises you?

01:07:00.395 --> 01:07:02.147
I was certain
Charon would have told you

01:07:02.147 --> 01:07:03.857
about my capacity for charity,

01:07:03.857 --> 01:07:06.234
especially for those
who prove themselves.

01:07:06.234 --> 01:07:07.986
He has, yes.

01:07:07.986 --> 01:07:11.656
I know he feels a great deal
of debt for all you've done

01:07:11.656 --> 01:07:13.366
and all you've yet to do.

01:07:13.366 --> 01:07:15.201
Oh, that's good to hear.

01:07:15.201 --> 01:07:17.287
He's just a boy,
so, you know, sometimes

01:07:17.287 --> 01:07:20.206
I worry that he might not
fully appreciate everything.

01:07:20.206 --> 01:07:21.708
But he does.

01:07:21.708 --> 01:07:24.085
You should have heard him
when I broached the idea

01:07:24.085 --> 01:07:25.628
of broadening his horizons.

01:07:25.628 --> 01:07:27.714
He was unequivocal,

01:07:27.714 --> 01:07:31.676
insisting his future
lies here...

01:07:31.676 --> 01:07:33.678
with you...

01:07:33.678 --> 01:07:35.889
nowhere else.

01:07:35.889 --> 01:07:39.059
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:07:39.059 --> 01:07:40.727
Perhaps
you could play something

01:07:40.727 --> 01:07:43.146
that speaks
to that faithfulness,

01:07:43.146 --> 01:07:44.981
that commitment.

01:07:44.981 --> 01:07:47.150
Does anything come to mind?

01:07:48.943 --> 01:07:55.408
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:07:55.408 --> 01:07:57.452
This is from "Don Giovanni."

01:07:57.452 --> 01:08:01.498
The theme of the whole piece
is "loyalty to the master."

01:08:03.041 --> 01:08:04.334
Wonderful.

01:08:04.334 --> 01:08:07.504
[cello playing]

01:08:07.504 --> 01:08:14.302
♪ ♪

01:08:36.116 --> 01:08:38.868
Right here is good.

01:08:38.868 --> 01:08:45.792
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:08:54.801 --> 01:08:56.553
Charon...

01:08:59.139 --> 01:09:01.808
Lovely to see you again.

01:09:02.767 --> 01:09:06.271
- So you're here for revenge?
- No. No, no, no, no, no.

01:09:06.271 --> 01:09:10.233
No, this is about justice

01:09:10.233 --> 01:09:13.236
And this is merely
a conversation.

01:09:13.236 --> 01:09:14.988
Relax.

01:09:14.988 --> 01:09:17.657
I'm just curious

01:09:17.657 --> 01:09:20.368
how Cormac talked
about my brother.

01:09:22.203 --> 01:09:25.206
He called him
a terrible thief.

01:09:26.374 --> 01:09:28.293
Well, Frankie was stealing
from Cormac

01:09:28.293 --> 01:09:30.211
even before we met him.

01:09:30.211 --> 01:09:32.297
In fact...
[inhales deeply]

01:09:32.297 --> 01:09:36.009
That's how we came to meet him.

01:09:36.009 --> 01:09:39.012
You were caught stealing?

01:09:39.012 --> 01:09:42.182
When we were kids, Frankie
did the little collection jobs.

01:09:42.182 --> 01:09:43.892
He would get a list
every Saturday

01:09:43.892 --> 01:09:45.852
and have to go around
the neighborhood.

01:09:45.852 --> 01:09:48.521
Everybody paid,
no questions asked.

01:09:48.521 --> 01:09:50.357
Frankie starts
skimming off the top,

01:09:50.357 --> 01:09:52.359
not so much
that anyone would notice,

01:09:52.359 --> 01:09:55.904
and this goes on
for a couple of weeks...

01:09:55.904 --> 01:09:59.532
until one night
our windshield explodes.

01:09:59.532 --> 01:10:01.576
You see, we were living
in a car.

01:10:01.576 --> 01:10:04.371
And we get dragged
through the broken glass,

01:10:04.371 --> 01:10:05.705
across the pavement,

01:10:05.705 --> 01:10:08.416
right to the feet
of you-know-who.

01:10:08.416 --> 01:10:12.045
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

01:10:12.045 --> 01:10:14.005
What did he do?

01:10:14.005 --> 01:10:15.256
I remember thinking,

01:10:15.256 --> 01:10:18.885
"This is the scariest man
I have ever seen."

01:10:18.885 --> 01:10:20.970
The first thing he did

01:10:20.970 --> 01:10:23.306
was point out that my shoes
were falling apart,

01:10:23.306 --> 01:10:26.059
as if I didn't have
any self-respect.

01:10:26.059 --> 01:10:29.813
And then he asked whose idea
was it, skimming from him.

01:10:29.813 --> 01:10:31.398
And Frankie tried
bullshitting him,

01:10:31.398 --> 01:10:33.858
so I chimed in
with the actual truth.

01:10:33.858 --> 01:10:36.069
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:10:36.069 --> 01:10:39.072
It was my idea.

01:10:39.072 --> 01:10:41.700
[breathes deeply]

01:10:41.700 --> 01:10:45.745
That was the moment
he saw something in us.

01:10:45.745 --> 01:10:49.416
That was the beginning
and the end.

01:10:49.416 --> 01:10:52.419
[cello playing]

01:10:52.419 --> 01:10:59.592
♪ ♪

01:11:05.807 --> 01:11:07.976
<i>What are you going to do
to me?</i>

01:11:07.976 --> 01:11:10.979
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

01:11:10.979 --> 01:11:15.900
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:11:15.900 --> 01:11:17.610
Help you.

01:11:17.610 --> 01:11:20.030
Can't you see you need help?

01:11:21.531 --> 01:11:23.241
[clears throat]

01:11:23.241 --> 01:11:25.493
[groans softly]

01:11:25.493 --> 01:11:29.247
With me, I was thrown
into the system

01:11:29.247 --> 01:11:30.582
and then sent away.

01:11:30.582 --> 01:11:32.542
So I invented a new persona,

01:11:32.542 --> 01:11:34.419
you know, something
to disguise me,

01:11:34.419 --> 01:11:36.338
but it was just a lie

01:11:36.338 --> 01:11:38.590
to hide myself
from my own shame,

01:11:38.590 --> 01:11:41.343
'cause the truth is,
I never got away from Cormac.

01:11:41.343 --> 01:11:44.179
He was the one who decided
what my life was,

01:11:44.179 --> 01:11:48.350
and now he's doing that to you.

01:11:50.518 --> 01:11:51.936
♪ ♪

01:11:51.936 --> 01:11:55.940
Keep playing.

01:11:55.940 --> 01:11:58.651
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:11:58.651 --> 01:12:01.696
Everyone's gonna miss
your music.

01:12:01.696 --> 01:12:04.866
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

01:12:04.866 --> 01:12:08.203
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:12:08.203 --> 01:12:10.497
I think I'll take a mulligan.

01:12:10.497 --> 01:12:13.458
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:12:13.458 --> 01:12:17.545
Join the club, you...

01:12:17.545 --> 01:12:20.507
motherfucker!

01:12:20.507 --> 01:12:25.136
You... take... my breath away.

01:12:25.136 --> 01:12:27.180
[yells]

01:12:27.180 --> 01:12:30.767
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:12:30.767 --> 01:12:34.938
I just got word that Cormac
has killed on hotel grounds.

01:12:37.232 --> 01:12:38.983
Do nothing.

01:12:38.983 --> 01:12:40.944
Tell no one.

01:12:40.944 --> 01:12:44.197
Let them eat each other,
and the coin press will emerge.

01:12:44.197 --> 01:12:47.200
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

01:12:47.200 --> 01:12:52.247
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:12:52.247 --> 01:12:54.666
<i>It may look like
we have nothing in common.</i>

01:12:56.584 --> 01:12:58.086
<i>Trust me.</i>

01:12:58.086 --> 01:13:00.964
<i>We are more alike
than we are different, Charon.</i>

01:13:06.177 --> 01:13:08.388
<i>Unfortunately,
I have a pretty good idea</i>

01:13:08.388 --> 01:13:11.349
<i>of what's in store.</i>

01:13:11.349 --> 01:13:14.060
<i>What I'm asking you to do
is not easy.</i>

01:13:14.060 --> 01:13:16.980
<i>It may go against everything
you stand for,</i>

01:13:16.980 --> 01:13:20.066
<i>your loyalty and your honesty,</i>

01:13:20.066 --> 01:13:22.610
<i>and it will mean
keeping secrets</i>

01:13:22.610 --> 01:13:24.946
<i>and telling lies
and breaking promises</i>

01:13:24.946 --> 01:13:29.242
<i>and sacrificing anything
he has promised you...</i>

01:13:29.242 --> 01:13:32.537
<i>like bringing your father to
The Continental, for example.</i>

01:13:32.537 --> 01:13:35.665
[indistinct chatter]

01:13:41.796 --> 01:13:44.007
<i>Did he ever punish you?</i>

01:13:44.007 --> 01:13:46.384
The first time you met,
when he caught you skimming?

01:13:46.384 --> 01:13:49.137
The next day I was in school
giving a book report,

01:13:49.137 --> 01:13:50.722
<i>and in walks
this terrifying man</i>

01:13:50.722 --> 01:13:51.890
<i>I'd never seen before.</i>

01:13:51.890 --> 01:13:54.476
He slams this box
on my teacher's desk

01:13:54.476 --> 01:13:57.562
and says to me,
"Open the fucking box."

01:13:57.562 --> 01:14:00.357
You know what was inside?

01:14:00.357 --> 01:14:02.567
[scoffs]

01:14:02.567 --> 01:14:04.402
A new pair of shoes.

01:14:04.402 --> 01:14:08.656
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:14:08.656 --> 01:14:11.659
<i>A father figure
is responsible</i>

01:14:11.659 --> 01:14:14.788
<i>for teaching you
about loyalty and family,</i>

01:14:14.788 --> 01:14:17.457
<i>relationships and business.</i>

01:14:17.457 --> 01:14:18.875
<i>And Cormac may preach this,</i>

01:14:18.875 --> 01:14:23.713
<i>but he only cares
about one thing--himself.</i>

01:14:23.713 --> 01:14:26.466
<i>And sooner or later,
you're gonna realize</i>

01:14:26.466 --> 01:14:29.636
<i>it's either you or him.</i>

01:14:29.636 --> 01:14:32.472
<i>I'm offering you a chance
to decide who you want to be</i>

01:14:32.472 --> 01:14:34.307
<i>before it's too late.</i>

01:14:34.307 --> 01:14:40.438
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:14:40.438 --> 01:14:43.108
[elevator bell dings]

01:14:43.108 --> 01:14:50.073
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:15:02.836 --> 01:15:07.590
[door opens, closes]

01:15:07.590 --> 01:15:14.764
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:15:36.369 --> 01:15:38.496
Our cellist friend...

01:15:38.496 --> 01:15:41.041
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:15:41.041 --> 01:15:45.211
Our, oh, so virtuous virtuoso...

01:15:45.211 --> 01:15:49.007
turned out
he was very disloyal.

01:15:49.007 --> 01:15:52.802
He tried to steal from me...

01:15:52.802 --> 01:15:57.390
and I am sick and tired
of people stealing from me.

01:15:57.390 --> 01:16:00.060
Oh, he confessed.

01:16:00.060 --> 01:16:02.812
As you can see,
I got pretty teed off.

01:16:02.812 --> 01:16:05.065
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:16:05.065 --> 01:16:07.525
Breach of trust
like this, well...

01:16:07.525 --> 01:16:10.612
it just makes me more grateful

01:16:10.612 --> 01:16:12.530
to those who remain loyal.

01:16:12.530 --> 01:16:14.699
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:16:14.699 --> 01:16:18.161
And with this in mind...

01:16:18.161 --> 01:16:20.205
ah...

01:16:20.205 --> 01:16:23.083
[scoffs, groans]

01:16:23.083 --> 01:16:26.878
I want our next musician
of residence

01:16:26.878 --> 01:16:29.714
to be someone that we know--

01:16:29.714 --> 01:16:33.426
an accomplished
international artist,

01:16:33.426 --> 01:16:35.470
and yet...

01:16:35.470 --> 01:16:39.349
someone who will fit in
more like a family member.

01:16:39.349 --> 01:16:41.601
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:16:41.601 --> 01:16:44.229
That's right--your father.

01:16:44.229 --> 01:16:46.398
[chuckles]

01:16:46.398 --> 01:16:47.816
Mm.

01:16:47.816 --> 01:16:50.235
What instrument
did your father play, again?

01:16:50.235 --> 01:16:54.447
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:16:54.447 --> 01:16:56.449
- Violin.
- Ah.

01:16:56.449 --> 01:16:58.660
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:16:58.660 --> 01:17:00.370
Sir, I--

01:17:00.370 --> 01:17:02.997
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:17:02.997 --> 01:17:05.792
Winston Scott
has assembled a team.

01:17:05.792 --> 01:17:07.585
They mean to kill you.

01:17:07.585 --> 01:17:09.796
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:17:09.796 --> 01:17:11.881
And how do you come
to know this?

01:17:13.508 --> 01:17:15.969
He asked me to join him.

01:17:15.969 --> 01:17:18.638
How did that make you feel?

01:17:18.638 --> 01:17:22.642
- It felt like an opportunity.
- Opportunity for what?

01:17:22.642 --> 01:17:24.978
An opportunity
for advancement.

01:17:24.978 --> 01:17:27.439
- Here with me?
- Indeed, sir.

01:17:27.439 --> 01:17:29.441
[sighs]

01:17:29.441 --> 01:17:30.734
Good man.

01:17:30.734 --> 01:17:33.653
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:17:33.653 --> 01:17:35.739
May I ask you
a question, sir?

01:17:35.739 --> 01:17:37.782
Sure.

01:17:37.782 --> 01:17:40.285
What was it that Thomas
was trying to steal?

01:17:40.285 --> 01:17:42.245
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:17:42.245 --> 01:17:43.538
You.

01:17:43.538 --> 01:17:46.624
<i>[Supertramp's
"Take the Long Way Home"]</i>

01:17:46.624 --> 01:17:52.589
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:17:52.589 --> 01:17:54.883
Loyalty.

01:17:54.883 --> 01:18:02.015
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:18:02.015 --> 01:18:05.018
<i>- * So you think
you're a Romeo ♪</i>

01:18:05.018 --> 01:18:07.228
<i>♪ You're playing a part
in a picture show ♪</i>

01:18:07.228 --> 01:18:10.190
<i>♪ Well, take
the long way home ♪</i>

01:18:10.190 --> 01:18:14.110
<i>♪ Take the long way home ♪</i>

01:18:14.110 --> 01:18:17.530
<i>♪ But you're the joke
of the neighborhood ♪</i>

01:18:17.530 --> 01:18:20.325
<i>♪ Why should you care
if you're feeling good? ♪</i>

01:18:20.325 --> 01:18:22.869
<i>♪ Well, take
the long way home ♪</i>

01:18:22.869 --> 01:18:26.873
<i>♪ Take the long way home ♪</i>

01:18:26.873 --> 01:18:28.333
<i>♪ There are times ♪</i>

01:18:28.333 --> 01:18:32.045
<i>♪ That you feel you're part
of the scenery ♪</i>

01:18:32.045 --> 01:18:35.215
<i>♪ All the greenery ♪</i>

01:18:35.215 --> 01:18:39.594
<i>♪ Is coming down, boy ♪</i>

01:18:39.594 --> 01:18:41.471
<i>♪ And then your wife
seems to think ♪</i>

01:18:41.471 --> 01:18:44.224
<i>♪ You're part
of the furniture ♪</i>

01:18:44.224 --> 01:18:47.727
<i>♪ Oh, it's peculiar ♪</i>

01:18:47.727 --> 01:18:53.400
<i>♪ She used to be so nice ♪</i>

01:18:53.400 --> 01:18:55.694
<i>♪ Oh, yeah ♪</i>

01:18:55.694 --> 01:19:00.824
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:19:00.824 --> 01:19:02.367
<i>Whoo!</i>

01:19:02.367 --> 01:19:06.121
<i>♪ ♪</i>
